      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/112082.Frans_de_Waal">About Frans de Waal</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/112082.Frans_de_Waal"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1222704792p3/112082.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/112082.Frans_de_Waal">Frans de Waal
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
1,269
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer11690170581179748765"><strong>Frans de Waal</strong> has been named one of <em>Time</em> magazine’s 100 Most Influential People. The author of <em>Are We Smart Enough to Know How Smart Animals Are?</em>, among many other works, he is the C. H. Candler Professor in Emory University’s Psychology Department and director of the Living Links Center at the Yerkes National Primate Research Center. He lives in Atlanta, Georgia.</span>

</div>
</div>

